{"id":4541,"date":"2023-12-08T15:40:35","date_gmt":"2023-12-08T04:40:35","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/?post_type=help_centre&#038;p=4541"},"modified":"2024-02-02T11:53:04","modified_gmt":"2024-02-02T00:53:04","slug":"broken-receiver-cable","status":"publish","type":"help_centre","link":"https:\/\/www.stokefoiling.com\/help-centre\/repairs\/broken-receiver-cable\/","title":{"rendered":"Broken Receiver Cable"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>If you find yourself with a broken receiver cable on the Stoke Foil Boost, follow these steps to address and resolve the issue:<\/p><ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><li>Identify the point on the main unit where the receiver cable is broken. This is typically near the entry point into the unit.<\/li>\n\n<li>Carefully remove the rubber seal from the main unit at the location where the receiver cable enters. Exercise caution to avoid scratching the unit or causing additional damage.<\/li>\n\n<li>After removing the rubber seal, you&#8217;ll likely find a small Phillips head or Allen screw securing the cable. Use an appropriate tool to remove this screw, freeing the cable for further examination and repair.<\/li>\n\n<li>Once the cable is accessible, locate the connectors along the cable that are positioned between two white alignment dots. These connectors secure the broken section of the cable. Disconnect the two connectors, effectively separating the damaged portion of the cable.<\/li><\/ol><figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<iframe title=\"Replacing the receiver on your Stoke Foil Boost\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/embed\/lc7Vyvm1Sjc?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" allowfullscreen><\/iframe>\n<\/div><\/figure>","protected":false},"excerpt":{